article_title: Hales Corners man dies while out bicycling
article_text:
By of the

A 54-year-old bicyclist died after suffering an apparent heart attack in Franklin Saturday evening, police said.

The Hales Corners man was not hit by a car as was initially suspected. His name was not released. The man was found at 5:20 p.m. in the 11900 block of W. Ryan Road and efforts to revive him were unsuccessful.
